Facts (layer 2):

`show` (VariableExpression):
  has bound(s) `Describe` `String` (resolved as `instance (Describe String)`)
  has type `String -> ()`
  is an expression
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `show :: value -> () where (Describe value)`

`show "Hello, world!"` (ExpressionStatement):
  has type `()`

`show "Hello, world!"` (CallExpression):
  has type `()`
  is an expression

`"Hello, world!"` (StringExpression):
  has type `String`
  is an expression


Output:
Hello, world!
